com.nhksos.quantumrex.Casino
Class CasinoManager

java.lang.Object
  org.bukkit.plugin.java.JavaPlugin
      com.nhksos.quantumrex.Casino.CasinoManager
All Implemented Interfaces:
CommandExecutor, Plugin
public class CasinoManager
extends JavaPlugin
implements Plugin

CasinoManager is the basic plugin management system for the casino system. It contains all functions that involve other plugins, and methods of interacting with, and sending data to, those plugins.

Currently, we have support for:

  • iConomy - the basic economy plugin. This plugin allows us to change a player's balance when he bets on a machine and wins.
  • Permissions - This plugin will allow us to control who on the server has access to the casino system. I plan to split up permissions into:
    • owners - people who can create casinos
    • players - people who can play games
    These permissions are completely independent. An owner is not automatically able to play games. This should hopefully prevent players from making intentionally broken machines that always pay out to increase their bank accounts.
  • Help - This is just a standard helper plugin. I don't really understand it at the moment, but I may implement support later.

Author:
quantumrex

onEnable

public void onEnable()
This method creates a DataManager for the plugin, and initializes the listeners that the plugin requires. It then registers the events this plugin listens to. If this method encounters any errors, it disables the plugin and reports that there was an error. I assume that if an error is encountered, it is during the loading of the database. So, rather than allowing the program to overwrite the previous successful database, the program halts, and it is up to the server administrator to discover the cause.

Specified by:
onEnable in interface Plugin

onCommand

public boolean onCommand(CommandSender sender,
                         Command command,
                         String label,
                         String[] args)
Almost all commands supported by this plugin are actually handled by the DataManager, because that is where most of the global data is actually stored and maintained. Commands are passed to it thru this method. In essence, this method checks whether the plugins required to perform the command are available, and if so, the command is executed.
